    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the wiring looks okay i think but there is this weird intermittent clicking sound coming from the unit too, like every few minutes. it's almost like something is clicking on and off randomly. does that sound like an electrical glitch or maybe something actually stuck in there?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An intermittent clicking sound could indicate an electrical component initiating and stopping, like a relay or capacitor engaging and disengaging. Relays, when failing, can make clicking sounds due to their internal contacts burning out. Of course, there's also the chance that something else might be stuck or obstructing the unit's internal moving parts, such as debris or debris. The unit's age should be taken into account, as older units are more prone to mechanical issues. \n\nSafety Note: You must turn off power to the unit to avoid the risk of electrical shock when investigating noises or sounds from an HVAC system. Given the intermittent nature of the sound and the unique issues you're describing, this would likely be more safely and accurately diagnosed by a professional technician. If the clicking is accompanied by the unit not running or turning off unexpectedly, call for a technician immediately as it could suggest a serious electrical problem.",
